cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.PL. 

This paper deals with the task of associating natural language comments with source code entities, which is a problem in software engineering. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as sequence labeling and binary classification, which are relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of supervised learning models and feature engineering suggests relevance to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the paper deals with Java source code, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
